genresAdvancedInfo.name: classical tuba
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre showcases the tuba as the main instrument, often in a solo or chamber music setting. The music is typically composed in the classical style, with an emphasis on the deep, rich sound of the tuba. Classical tuba music is known for its complexity, technical skill, and expressive power, and is often featured in orchestral and brass band music.
